How to run Linux on the board
Start Linux from SD
Altera

    Start the board and (eventually) interrupt the auto boot
    Be sure the following env variables are set:

    %> pri ipaddr
    %> pri ethaddr


    In case set it as follow

    %> setenv ipaddr 192.168.89.200
    %> setenv ethaddr "84:39:BE:52:00:74" 

    Be sure the following env variables are set:

    %> pri bootimage
    %> pri fdtimage


    Be sure they are set to the correct values

    %> setenv bootimage zImage
    %> setenv fdtimage system_altera.dtb

    Consider the command "mmcload", running "%> pri mmcload" it should return

    mmc rescan;${mmcloadcmd} mmc 0:${mmcloadpart} ${loadaddr} ${bootimage};${mmcloadcmd} mmc 0:${mmcloadpart} ${fdtaddr} ${fdtimage}

    Run mmcload command

    %> run mmcload


    The result should be something like:

    reading zImage
    4870088 bytes read in 276 ms (16.8 MiB/s)
    reading system_altera.dtb
    21437 bytes read in 7 ms (2.9 MiB/s)

    Run Linux

    %> run mmcboot


